**Root cause:** The loop condition was `i < items.length - 1`, which stops at the second-to-last index, skipping the final element entirely.

**Fix:** Changed to `i < items.length` so the loop iterates over all indices, including the last one.

```ts
// Before (buggy)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

